n and Learning in Pre-Service Teacher Education -- tPart 4: Addressing Established Paradigms -- t11. NESTs Versus Non-NESTs: Rethinking English-Language Teacher Identitie -- t12. Multilingualism Pedagogy: Building Bridges between Languages -- tSubject Index -- tName Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume addresses the complex issues surrounding language teacher education, especially in EFL, and the development of professionalism in this field. By applying such concepts as Shulman's "pedagogical content knowledge", the development of teachers' knowledge base is investigated in a variety of settings, thus underpinning the contextual nature of teacher learning. The vital role of critical reflection at all stages of teacher development is shown to be an integral part of language teachers' knowledge constructions in areas such as pedagogical grammar, assessment and testing. The contributions shed light also on the perception and development of teacher expertise. This volume sets out to bridge the gap between theory and practice, and in so doing shows that these constructs are far from monolithic. Rather, both theory and practice are created and developed dynamically in close interrelation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish language -- Study and teaching -- Foreign speakers. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aEnglish teachers -- Training of. 0aEnglish teachersxTraining of. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh  aEFL.  aShulman.  aknowledge construction.  alanguage teacher education.  apedagogical content knowledge.  ateacher development.  atheory and practice.1 aAppel, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerger, 